and no one eats
the grilled cheese.

20
00:00:45,838 --> 00:00:47,573
She's having one.

21
00:00:47,725 --> 00:00:50,611
Well, of course Fat Carol is eating one.
What do you expect?

22
00:00:50,626 --> 00:00:52,610
Anyway, so how does this work?

23
00:00:52,628 --> 00:00:54,401
You have to work the room.

24
00:00:54,417 --> 00:00:55,443
"Work the room"?

25
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:58,182
Circulate, baby.
Introduce yourself.

26
00:00:58,197 --> 00:01:01,042
We want everyone to meet you.

27
00:01:01,058 --> 00:01:03,371
Okay. Wish me luck.

28
00:01:03,388 --> 00:01:04,853
Bye.

29
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:08,683
I'm sorry.

30
00:01:10,957 --> 00:01:12,572
It--it--it's my first time.

31
00:01:12,588 --> 00:01:15,182
More classic moments for
Betty's wall of shame.

32
00:01:16,877 --> 00:01:19,562
Hi. Excuse me.

33
00:01:19,905 --> 00:01:22,622
We haven't officially met.
Um, I'm Betty Suarez.

34
00:01:22,637 --> 00:01:24,561
I work at "Mode," too.

35
00:01:26,807 --> 00:01:29,462
I always thought I'd
be good at your job.

36
00:01:29,775 --> 00:01:31,593
How long do you
think you'll last?

37
00:01:31,606 --> 00:01:35,710
Well, unless you know something
that I don't, a while, I hope.

38
00:01:36,246 --> 00:01:37,821
That's too bad.

39
00:01:38,418 --> 00:01:41,321
You know, I love that you're
having a grilled cheese.

40
00:01:41,338 --> 00:01:43,350
Most people at
"Mode" don't eat.

41
00:01:45,517 --> 00:01:47,663
Sometimes they shouldn't.

42
00:01:52,065 --> 00:01:53,473
Just a minute.

43
00:01:55,846 --> 00:01:59,173
Carlo Medina. I work with the
editor in chief at "Isabella."

44
00:01:59,186 --> 00:02:02,112
Oh, Betty Suarez,
assistant to Daniel Meade at "Mode."

45
00:02:02,127 --> 00:02:03,713
Oh, I know who you are.

46
00:02:03,727 --> 00:02:05,581
You're a legend.

47
00:02:08,405 --> 00:02:11,902
Housekeeping swears they
haven't seen a red music box.

48
00:02:11,915 --> 00:02:13,642
Any luck?

49
00:02:13,858 --> 00:02:16,160
Does it look like
I've had any luck?

50
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:18,522
Daniel and Wilhelmina
are still waiting for you

51
00:02:18,538 --> 00:02:20,883
to sign off on the
holiday spread.

52
00:02:20,898 --> 00:02:22,323
What?

53
00:02:22,535 --> 00:02:23,842
Oh.

54
00:02:28,807 --> 00:02:30,163
Keep looking.

55
00:02:37,678 --> 00:02:41,441
Seem to be a lot of layers.
I'd like to see more skin.

56
00:02:41,457 --> 00:02:45,433
It's a postnuclear scene. Exposed
skin would melt off their bodies.

57
00:02:45,446 --> 00:02:46,480
My bad.

58
00:02:46,498 --> 00:02:48,691
I understand you have a
holiday spread for me.

59
00:02:48,707 --> 00:02:51,503
Yeah. Yes, we do.
We think you're gonna like it.

60
00:02:51,906 --> 00:02:56,052
In this world of global
warming and political unrest,

61
00:02:56,066 --> 00:02:59,733
we give you a
postapocalyptic Christmas.

62
00:02:59,746 --> 00:03:01,883
A "Mad Max-mas" if you will.

63
00:03:01,898 --> 00:03:05,253
I discovered this designer
out of Vietnam-- Anh Vu-Tran--

64
00:03:05,265 --> 00:03:07,670
so hot,
no one in the states knows about her.

65
00:03:07,685 --> 00:03:11,432
She's doing an exclusive line
of flak jackets just for us.

66
00:03:11,445 --> 00:03:13,702
We got all the props and
equipment on hold for thursday.

67
00:03:13,715 --> 00:03:15,121
We just need to
pull the trigger.

68
00:03:15,136 --> 00:03:16,491
So let's walk you
through the mock-ups,

69
00:03:16,527 --> 00:03:17,832
show you what we have in mind.

70
00:03:17,846 --> 00:03:19,621
Yeah, sounds good.

71
00:03:19,637 --> 00:03:21,573
Uh, I have to get
back upstairs.

72
00:03:26,556 --> 00:03:28,630
He was disturbed?

73
00:03:28,648 --> 00:03:31,383
He looked very disturbed.

74
00:03:31,396 --> 00:03:34,203
Mm. He should.

75
00:03:34,337 --> 00:03:37,063
He  got sloppy.

76
00:03:37,097 --> 00:03:38,832
And we got...

77
00:03:38,847 --> 00:03:40,921
a music box.

78
00:03:46,847 --> 00:03:48,610
Sorry I'm late!

79
00:03:48,626 --> 00:03:51,232
I hope you guys didn't
wait for me to eat dinner.

80
00:03:52,638 --> 00:03:54,003
What are you doing here?

81
00:03:54,018 --> 00:03:56,341
- Tuesday's tamale night.
- We broke up.

82
00:03:56,357 --> 00:03:58,480
Walter always comes
on tamale night.

83
00:03:58,497 --> 00:04:03,233
He cheated on me. I'm not sure
I'm ready to just jump back in.

84
00:04:03,248 --> 00:04:04,430
It's tamale night.

85
00:04:04,445 --> 00:04:07,292
Betty, I didn't raise
you to be rude to guests.

86
00:04:07,308 --> 00:04:10,293
Now we saved you some tamales.

87
00:04:10,305 --> 00:04:12,572
Okay. Thank you. I'm starving.

88
00:04:12,588 --> 00:04:14,710
I went to this really
cool work thing tonight,

89
00:04:14,726 --> 00:04:17,001
except it's not
professional to eat, so

90
00:04:17,017 --> 00:04:18,822
I just had a mango margarita.

91
00:04:18,837 --> 00:04:20,121
Here you go.

92
00:04:20,137 --> 00:04:21,053
Hey.

93
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:22,702
Dad, you know what
the doctor said.

94
00:04:22,717 --> 00:04:24,302
You can't have coffee.

95
00:04:24,858 --> 00:04:27,772
Anyway, so I spent the entire
evening just networking

96
00:04:27,787 --> 00:04:30,342
and giving out my
business cards.

97
00:04:30,828 --> 00:04:32,750
- What?
- What? Nothing.

98
00:04:32,765 --> 00:04:35,630
It's just, I find it interesting.
You're drinking now. Okay.

99
00:04:35,645 --> 00:04:37,380
You used to get woozy
from your astringent.

100
00:04:37,397 --> 00:04:39,113
Anyway, it was really fun,

101
00:04:39,127 --> 00:04:41,850
and I finally felt
like I belonged.

102
00:04:42,046 --> 00:04:44,370
- You're a legend.
- Me?

103
00:04:44,385 --> 00:04:47,160
You saved the Fabia layout
in your first week.

104
00:04:47,177 --> 00:04:49,871
Oh, no. No, no, no, no.
It didn't happen like that.

105
00:04:49,886 --> 00:04:52,933
I've slaved away for years, and I'm
not even trusted to pick out a belt.

106
00:04:52,946 --> 00:04:54,843
What is your secret?

107
00:04:54,855 --> 00:04:58,883
Um... just, uh, doing my job.

108
00:04:59,477 --> 00:05:01,902
And she's modest, too.

109
00:05:02,656 --> 00:05:03,902
What are you drinking?

110
00:05:03,916 --> 00:05:05,323
Um...

111
00:05:05,336 --> 00:05:07,603
uh,  mango margarita?

112
00:05:08,207 --> 00:05:11,612
Oh, you should have seen her.
She was so gross.

113
00:05:11,626 --> 00:05:14,281
All she did was talk about
herself the entire night.

114
00:05:14,298 --> 00:05:15,792
Yeah, that doesn't
sound like Betty.

115
00:05:15,805 --> 00:05:18,691
Ugh. Well, get a drink in her,
and it is the Betty show.

116
00:05:18,707 --> 00:05:22,332
She would not shut up,
bragging about the Fabia layout.

117
00:05:22,345 --> 00:05:23,541
It was all Daniel's vision.

118
00:05:23,555 --> 00:05:26,761
It'd be really wrong for me to
take any credit for the layout.

119
00:05:26,778 --> 00:05:30,661
Wow. An assistant who doesn't
trash-talk their boss.

120
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:34,632
I know.
Trash-talking is what I do best.

121
00:05:34,645 --> 00:05:37,331
Well, second best.

122
00:05:37,348 --> 00:05:39,420
It's really easy when
you have a good boss.

123
00:05:39,437 --> 00:05:41,990
You know, I'm really,
really lucky to work for Daniel.

124
00:05:42,007 --> 00:05:45,822
And she was clueless as
to how to handle herself.

125
00:05:45,837 --> 00:05:46,942
Shock. 

126
00:05:46,957 --> 00:05:50,371
You should have seen when she
pulled out her business cards.

127
00:05:50,385 --> 00:05:51,801
I just got 'em today.

128
00:05:51,815 --> 00:05:54,920
I don't usually carry
entire boxes in my purse.

129
00:05:54,937 --> 00:05:58,300
Well, not since kleenex came
out with the travel size.

130
00:05:58,316 --> 00:05:59,313
No, they did.

131
00:05:59,326 --> 00:06:00,662
Tragic.

132
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:03,583
They're laughing at you,
Betty, not with you.

133
00:06:03,826 --> 00:06:05,742
Poor cow has no idea
we only invited her

134
00:06:05,755 --> 00:06:07,732
so people could see
she really exists.

135
00:06:07,746 --> 00:06:09,661
She's  like the real
life Snuffleupagus....

136
00:06:09,676 --> 00:06:11,372
- only hairier.
- Marc!

137
00:06:11,387 --> 00:06:14,081
What did you find out
that's useful to me?!

138
00:06:14,105 --> 00:06:16,003
No choice gossip?

139
00:06:16,016 --> 00:06:19,132
No dirt to help me destroy
any lesser magazine?

140
00:06:19,147 --> 00:06:22,582
Uh, I, uh,
I'll do better next time.

141
00:06:25,415 --> 00:06:29,392
Do you know how many curly-haired,
effete sycophants there are

142
00:06:29,407 --> 00:06:31,072
waiting to replace you?

143
00:06:31,085 --> 00:06:33,350
I know.
You have five of them on speed dial.

144
00:06:33,363 --> 00:06:35,415
Don't make me call.

145
00:06:42,378 --> 00:06:45,079
Anyway, it was an
amazing night.

146
00:06:45,089 --> 00:06:46,611
Are you gonna eat that?

147
00:06:47,079 --> 00:06:49,152
Oh, right. I forgot.

148
00:06:49,168 --> 00:06:52,300
You probably need it
to soak up the booze.

149
00:06:52,847 --> 00:06:56,291
You know what?
You'd be perfect for my school project.

150
00:06:56,306 --> 00:06:57,581
What school project?

151
00:06:57,596 --> 00:06:59,351
They gave us an assignment
today to write a paper

152
00:06:59,387 --> 00:07:01,292
about someone whose
job we admire.

153
00:07:01,307 --> 00:07:04,081
We get the whole day off
tomorrow to go observe them.

154
00:07:04,097 --> 00:07:05,592
Can you take me to "Mode"?

155
00:07:05,606 --> 00:07:08,472
Yeah, of course,
if it's okay with your mom.

156
00:07:08,485 --> 00:07:10,772
You know,
the fashion world isn't that great.

157
00:07:10,787 --> 00:07:13,060
It's a bunch of self-serving,
shallow tramps

158
00:07:13,077 --> 00:07:16,441
who starve themselves and backstab
each other for expensive clothes,

159
00:07:16,457 --> 00:07:19,512
no self-respecting person
would be caught dead in.

160
00:07:20,956 --> 00:07:22,840
So can I go?

161
00:07:24,415 --> 00:07:26,651
Well, don't say I
didn't warn you.

162
00:07:34,325 --> 00:07:36,830
Oh, my god. You're a celebrity!

163
00:07:36,848 --> 00:07:39,501
The Meade security
guard knows your name!

164
00:07:40,747 --> 00:07:42,992
Oh, look,
here are some of my friends.

165
00:07:43,008 --> 00:07:45,852
Just because we're sharing an
elevator doesn't mean we're friends.

166
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:49,050
Marc, Amanda,
this is, uh, Justin.

167
00:07:49,605 --> 00:07:52,531
Oh, so that's pregnancy weight.

168
00:07:52,545 --> 00:07:55,232
No, um, he's my nephew.

169
00:07:56,288 --> 00:07:58,302
Oh, my god.

170
00:07:58,317 --> 00:08:01,092
Manolo Blahniks, spring 2004!

171
00:08:04,055 --> 00:08:06,913
Wearing two-year-old shoes.

172
00:08:07,046 --> 00:08:09,431
Even I didn't catch that.

173
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:11,363
Definitely not your son.

174
00:08:12,087 --> 00:08:13,982
I got nothin'! I hate this.

175
00:08:14,578 --> 00:08:16,432
Don't take it out
on the furniture.

176
00:08:16,447 --> 00:08:19,471
It's late october. I got to shoot
the holiday spread this week...

177
00:08:19,486 --> 00:08:22,081
- It's the tube!
- Shh, Justin!

178
00:08:22,095 --> 00:08:23,270
- Sorry.
- Go sit at my desk.

179
00:08:23,288 --> 00:08:24,332
It's right there.

180
00:08:24,348 --> 00:08:27,670
I went to go get
the tanks--gone!

181
00:08:27,686 --> 00:08:30,511
I went to book
the models-- gone!

182
00:08:30,527 --> 00:08:33,523
I went to gethe burned
out Christmas trees--gone!

183
00:08:33,536 --> 00:08:35,833
"Isabella" took them
all out from under us.

184
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:37,041
- Calm down.
- How can I calm down

185
00:08:37,075 --> 00:08:38,913
when somebody leaked our ideas?

186
00:08:38,928 --> 00:08:42,513
"Isabella" magazine literally
stole our entire feature spread!

187
00:08:42,527 --> 00:08:44,271
Oh, my god.

188
00:08:44,285 --> 00:08:46,012
C-Carlo Medina.

189
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,972
He bought me a drink.

190
00:08:51,157 --> 00:08:54,040
Transcript : Raceman
Subtitles : Willow's Team

191
00:08:54,258 --> 00:08:56,042
www.forom.com

192
00:09:03,665 --> 00:09:08,303
"Isabella" magazine is doing
a postapocalyptic Christmas.

193
00:09:08,316 --> 00:09:11,391
They copied our entire concept.

194
00:09:11,405 --> 00:09:13,240
They didn't just copy it.
They took it.

195
00:09:13,258 --> 00:09:16,862
The holiday issue is our biggest
source of ad revenue for the year.

196
00:09:16,878 --> 00:09:18,161
We lose advertisers.

197
00:09:18,178 --> 00:09:20,143
Our circulation
goes in the toilet.

198
00:09:20,155 --> 00:09:24,562
Which is precisely why "Mode"
does not tolerate leaks.

199
00:09:24,575 --> 00:09:27,231
Now I will give the
guilty party one chance

200
00:09:27,246 --> 00:09:29,522
to come forward and confess.

201
00:09:29,797 --> 00:09:35,480
Did any of you speak to
anyone at "Isabella"?

202
00:09:51,006 --> 00:09:53,661
Well, then, cowards,
we'll do it the hard way.

203
00:09:53,678 --> 00:09:55,482
Everyone is considered guilty

204
00:09:55,498 --> 00:09:57,332
and will be treated as such

205
00:09:57,345 --> 00:09:59,633
until there's a confession.

206
00:09:59,848 --> 00:10:03,532
But by noon on thursday,
someone's head will roll.

207
00:10:07,645 --> 00:10:10,393
See who entered and
exited the building.

208
00:10:10,406 --> 00:10:14,270
I left Fey's music box on my desk,
and now it's gone.

209
00:10:14,287 --> 00:10:15,792
Investigate  everyone.

210
00:10:15,808 --> 00:10:17,321
You have to find
out who took it.

211
00:10:17,336 --> 00:10:18,863
Why didn't you burn it
with the other things?

212
00:10:18,896 --> 00:10:20,111
I couldn't.

213
00:10:20,126 --> 00:10:21,583
That music box is personal.

214
00:10:21,595 --> 00:10:23,191
But it connects you to Fey.

215
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:24,820
It could provide a motive.

216
00:10:24,837 --> 00:10:26,812
Who knows about the affair?

217
00:10:26,896 --> 00:10:28,451
No one.

218
00:10:28,865 --> 00:10:31,213
No one but my wife.

219
00:10:31,428 --> 00:10:34,662
We have two days to
conceive and execute

220
00:10:34,678 --> 00:10:36,631
an entirely new concept.

221
00:10:36,647 --> 00:10:39,793
If any of you have any plans,
I need you to cancel 'em.

222
00:10:39,808 --> 00:10:42,362
I want everyone working
together to pull this off.

223
00:10:42,378 --> 00:10:45,510
What Daniel's trying to say is
kiss your loved ones good-bye

224
00:10:45,525 --> 00:10:47,821
and expect to come
home to dead pets.

225
00:10:47,838 --> 00:10:48,803
Schmoopy.

226
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:50,771
Well, what are you waiting for?

227
00:10:56,148 --> 00:11:00,331
You kicked me with your
two-year-old shoes!

228
00:11:03,877 --> 00:11:06,790
Have something to be
nervous about, Carol?

229
00:11:06,965 --> 00:11:09,203
I ate half a bagel.

230
00:11:13,066 --> 00:11:16,373
All three of us talked to Carlo
Medina from "Isabella" last night.

231
00:11:16,386 --> 00:11:18,270
What exactly did you tell him?

232
00:11:18,285 --> 00:11:20,312
Not that much.

233
00:11:20,328 --> 00:11:22,293
So you can tell me,

234
00:11:22,305 --> 00:11:24,233
is Daniel Meade a
complete incompetent

235
00:11:24,245 --> 00:11:27,351
or more like a slow-but-cute
younger brother?

236
00:11:27,366 --> 00:11:28,621
Neither.

237
00:11:28,636 --> 00:11:31,230
Daniel is a lot smarter
than people think he is.

238
00:11:31,245 --> 00:11:34,090
Really? I just find that
so hard to believe.

239
00:11:34,105 --> 00:11:36,450
Okay, well, like thursday,
we have our feature shoot--

240
00:11:36,466 --> 00:11:39,410
a postapocalyptic Christmas.
It's really cool.

241
00:11:39,426 --> 00:11:42,981
We rented tanks,
and it was all Daniel's idea. Tanks.

242
00:11:42,997 --> 00:11:44,770
Ooh, Betty. Too bad.
It looks like you're the leak.

243
00:11:44,805 --> 00:11:46,390
Oh, well.
You didn't really fit in here anyway.

244
00:11:46,428 --> 00:11:47,651
- Ta.
- Wait, no!

245
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:49,121
All I mentioned were tanks.

246
00:11:49,138 --> 00:11:50,710
You guys talked to him, too.

247
00:11:50,726 --> 00:11:54,271
Yeah, what did you
talk to Carlo about?

248
00:11:54,285 --> 00:11:57,721
Okay, first of all,
he talked to me.

249
00:11:58,617 --> 00:12:00,630
To assistants.

250
00:12:04,647 --> 00:12:06,553
What are you doing
