505
00:25:46,786 --> 00:25:50,653
So this is very...
flea market chic.

506
00:25:50,668 --> 00:25:53,640
Ah, these must be your friends from,
uh, "The Mode."

507
00:25:53,658 --> 00:25:55,260
Just "Mode," dad.

508
00:25:55,275 --> 00:25:58,913
Um, this is my father
Ignacio and my sister Hilda.

509
00:25:58,927 --> 00:26:00,811
Ho-la.

510
00:26:01,007 --> 00:26:03,523
It's, uh, "hola."

511
00:26:03,536 --> 00:26:04,432
No.

512
00:26:04,447 --> 00:26:06,033
There's an "h" in it.

513
00:26:06,048 --> 00:26:07,333
Betty?

514
00:26:07,348 --> 00:26:11,213
This lotion is made from
crushed diamonds and...

515
00:26:11,225 --> 00:26:13,943
Hey, guys.
I didn't know you were here.

516
00:26:13,958 --> 00:26:15,650
Nice. You stole the good stuff.

517
00:26:15,668 --> 00:26:16,980
Justin.

518
00:26:17,008 --> 00:26:18,603
Homework.

519
00:26:23,036 --> 00:26:26,052
Oh, um...
Amanda, those are plastic.

520
00:26:26,068 --> 00:26:27,130
Ew.

521
00:26:27,148 --> 00:26:30,041
Betty, maybe we should
offer your friends a snack.

522
00:26:30,055 --> 00:26:31,411
We have flan.

523
00:26:31,427 --> 00:26:32,981
What's a flan?

524
00:26:32,996 --> 00:26:34,860
It's a delicious custard.

525
00:26:34,875 --> 00:26:36,932
Oh, bring it.

526
00:26:48,307 --> 00:26:53,641
How about a "Lawrence
of Arabia" Christmas?

527
00:26:53,657 --> 00:26:55,243
I don't even know
what that means.

528
00:26:55,256 --> 00:27:00,902
It means that we can use the 21 tons
of sand that are already there.

529
00:27:06,528 --> 00:27:11,712
Okay. All right.
Off that, the sand...

530
00:27:11,775 --> 00:27:15,491
is desert sand like Africa,
so maybe instead of Christmas,

531
00:27:15,505 --> 00:27:17,993
we do other winter
holidays. Kwanzaa?

532
00:27:18,007 --> 00:27:20,062
Did you just gesture at
me when you said Kwanzaa?

533
00:27:20,075 --> 00:27:21,431
No.

534
00:27:31,825 --> 00:27:33,713
How about this?

535
00:27:34,295 --> 00:27:36,113
Fey's sleigh ride--

536
00:27:36,127 --> 00:27:39,071
the biggest-selling holiday
issue in the history of "Mode."

537
00:27:39,087 --> 00:27:40,561
1986.

538
00:27:40,576 --> 00:27:42,141
Yeah, I know it well.

539
00:27:42,155 --> 00:27:43,721
Let me see that.

540
00:27:47,075 --> 00:27:49,403
It's traditional. I like it.

541
00:27:49,417 --> 00:27:51,053
Old is the new new.

542
00:27:51,068 --> 00:27:53,962
When Fey put herself in the photo,
it sent shock waves.

543
00:27:53,978 --> 00:27:56,581
No editor ever appeared
in the center spread.

544
00:27:56,598 --> 00:27:58,861
I think in the
year of her death,

545
00:27:58,877 --> 00:28:02,502
an empty sleigh would
be a nice tribute.

546
00:28:06,745 --> 00:28:08,683
What do you think?

547
00:28:08,876 --> 00:28:10,393
Yeah.

548
00:28:10,547 --> 00:28:12,773
Let's do it.

549
00:28:14,125 --> 00:28:15,773
We're pinning it on Fat Carol.

550
00:28:15,785 --> 00:28:16,382
What?

551
00:28:16,395 --> 00:28:18,373
Well, we have to say something
when Wilhelmina calls us in.

552
00:28:18,406 --> 00:28:20,733
Marc, that's not fair.
She didn't do anything.

553
00:28:20,748 --> 00:28:22,602
You know she calls you
"Fat Betty," right?

554
00:28:22,618 --> 00:28:25,191
See? This is why I hate secrets
because they turn into lies,

555
00:28:25,205 --> 00:28:26,282
which are much worse.

556
00:28:26,296 --> 00:28:27,561
Fat Carol hates her job.

557
00:28:27,575 --> 00:28:30,240
Would she eat so many
grilled cheeses if she cared?

558
00:28:30,255 --> 00:28:31,953
Betty, we're doing
this for you.

559
00:28:31,967 --> 00:28:34,081
We could get other jobs, but

560
00:28:34,097 --> 00:28:36,293
look how long it took
you to land this one.

561
00:28:36,307 --> 00:28:38,371
Well, I just didn't realize
that keeping so many secrets

562
00:28:38,408 --> 00:28:41,032
was such a big part of
my job description.

563
00:28:41,257 --> 00:28:43,043
Betty...

564
00:28:44,527 --> 00:28:47,673
do you have another
pan of this stuff?

565
00:28:53,475 --> 00:28:55,703
You're disgusting.

566
00:28:58,257 --> 00:29:01,103
Healthy appetite that girl has.

567
00:29:01,927 --> 00:29:04,491
Don't tell her we
have ice cream.

568
00:29:10,547 --> 00:29:12,311
You know, Betty...

569
00:29:13,208 --> 00:29:15,240
sometimes...

570
00:29:15,255 --> 00:29:18,313
we have to keep
secrets to survive.

571
00:29:34,618 --> 00:29:35,943
Hold it!

572
00:29:42,226 --> 00:29:45,270
You know, it's too bad about
your Wilhelmina meeting.

573
00:29:45,566 --> 00:29:47,941
We'll miss you around here.

574
00:29:48,755 --> 00:29:51,013
Shut up, Carol.

575
00:29:51,028 --> 00:29:55,863
I don't know if there's rehab for...
whatever this is,

576
00:29:55,877 --> 00:29:58,731
but consider it before
starting the job hunt.

577
00:29:58,747 --> 00:30:02,892
And, Betty,
I think I might miss you most of all.

578
00:30:03,537 --> 00:30:06,092
It was nice having
someone Fatter than me.

579
00:30:07,505 --> 00:30:09,301
Fat Carol.

580
00:30:09,638 --> 00:30:11,292
Fat Carol.

581
00:30:12,906 --> 00:30:14,752
Fat Carol.

582
00:30:18,785 --> 00:30:21,060
Good morning, Daniel.
Here's your coffee.

583
00:30:21,077 --> 00:30:23,823
I didn't realize you were
gonna come in so early.

584
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:29,423
Where'd you get that?

585
00:30:29,438 --> 00:30:32,600
Are you okay?
Do you need me to get you something?

586
00:30:35,336 --> 00:30:37,462
When I was 12,

587
00:30:37,806 --> 00:30:39,930
I had the worst
Christmas of my life.

588
00:30:39,945 --> 00:30:41,492
My, uh...

589
00:30:41,595 --> 00:30:44,162
father had just gotten
back from Switzerland,

590
00:30:44,176 --> 00:30:46,852
brought my mom... a music box.

591
00:30:46,866 --> 00:30:48,770
Exactly like this.

592
00:30:48,787 --> 00:30:50,791
She loved it.

593
00:30:50,847 --> 00:30:55,553
A few days later,
she hid the thing in the attic...

594
00:30:57,756 --> 00:31:02,673
set fire to a thousand
copies of "Mode" magazine.

595
00:31:02,807 --> 00:31:05,551
No one would ever tell me why.

596
00:31:05,565 --> 00:31:07,823
So is this your mother's?

597
00:31:07,836 --> 00:31:11,392
No. This...
appeared here this morning.

598
00:31:11,406 --> 00:31:13,840
Apparently my father
bought two of them--

599
00:31:13,856 --> 00:31:16,070
one for his wife

600
00:31:16,085 --> 00:31:18,923
and, uh, one...

601
00:31:23,367 --> 00:31:25,470
For his mistress.

602
00:31:27,058 --> 00:31:30,701
That's why Fey put herself
in the feature spread.

603
00:31:31,035 --> 00:31:34,341
She was flaunting the
affair in my mother's face.

604
00:31:34,357 --> 00:31:36,750
I'm sorry, Daniel.

605
00:31:37,886 --> 00:31:40,501
Was there anything inside?

606
00:31:42,598 --> 00:31:44,980
You know, the top lifts out.

607
00:31:55,595 --> 00:31:59,081
This woman is trying to connect
your father to Fey Sommers.

608
00:31:59,095 --> 00:32:00,391
She's trying to do
more than that, Betty.

609
00:32:00,426 --> 00:32:03,852
She's trying to connect
my dad to Fey's death.

610
00:32:05,656 --> 00:32:07,202
I just got back
from the studio.

611
00:32:07,216 --> 00:32:09,521
There's still 21 tons
of sand sitting there.

612
00:32:09,537 --> 00:32:11,251
Maybe I should just go
to the paramus mall

613
00:32:11,267 --> 00:32:13,931
and take pictures
of kids with Santa.

614
00:32:15,887 --> 00:32:18,960
No. I know what we
can do with that sand.

615
00:32:18,976 --> 00:32:21,051
Follow me to the art department.
Come on.

616
00:32:21,068 --> 00:32:22,922
Wait. Daniel?

617
00:32:23,015 --> 00:32:24,872
You should probably know
that I have a meeting

618
00:32:24,887 --> 00:32:27,490
with Wilhelmina
in five minutes.

619
00:32:28,357 --> 00:32:30,551
Really? You?

620
00:32:30,566 --> 00:32:33,512
Yeah, me and--and
Amanda and Marc.

621
00:32:33,526 --> 00:32:35,640
You sure you know
what you're doing?

622
00:32:35,658 --> 00:32:37,312
Not a clue.

623
00:32:37,328 --> 00:32:39,381
Just be careful what you say.

624
00:32:45,158 --> 00:32:47,182
Justin, what are
you doing here?

625
00:32:47,197 --> 00:32:49,732
I have to do some more
research for my paper.

626
00:32:49,747 --> 00:32:51,910
Sit down. Thank you, Marc.

627
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:54,923
Daniel Meade's office.

628
00:32:54,935 --> 00:32:57,622
Justin's school just called.
He's not there. Is he with you?

629
00:32:57,638 --> 00:32:59,373
Yeah, he's--he's right here.

630
00:32:59,388 --> 00:33:00,800
I'm gonna kill him.

631
00:33:00,817 --> 00:33:02,713
I knew this would happen.

632
00:33:02,727 --> 00:33:05,180
The fashion world is no
place for a boy his age.

633
00:33:05,197 --> 00:33:07,491
Well, he said he has to do
more work for his paper.

634
00:33:07,507 --> 00:33:10,253
Wake up, Betty.
There is no paper.

635
00:33:10,265 --> 00:33:11,242
What?

636
00:33:11,257 --> 00:33:13,911
Yeah, he made the whe thing up
so he could just ditch school

637
00:33:13,928 --> 00:33:15,902
and spend time in your world.

638
00:33:15,917 --> 00:33:17,192
Well, I didn't know.

639
00:33:17,205 --> 00:33:18,562
I don't even know
how to deal with it.

640
00:33:18,598 --> 00:33:20,942
I don't--I don't know what
I'm gonna do with that boy.

641
00:33:20,955 --> 00:33:25,403
You tell him that he is in
big trouble when he gets home.

642
00:33:27,508 --> 00:33:30,440
So... you're ditching?

643
00:33:30,456 --> 00:33:33,371
It's not a big deal.
I'm missing P.E. and art.

644
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:34,840
We're sketching fruit.

645
00:33:34,855 --> 00:33:36,493
That's not the point.

646
00:33:36,507 --> 00:33:39,901
Justin, this place that you
think is so glamorous...

647
00:33:39,918 --> 00:33:42,003
it's not all it's
cracked up to be.

648
00:33:42,016 --> 00:33:45,921
It's people deceiving each other and...
hiding things

649
00:33:45,936 --> 00:33:50,482
and all kinds of stuff that's
not good for a kid to be around.

650
00:33:50,497 --> 00:33:53,150
Someday, maybe you'll end up
working in a place like this,

651
00:33:53,168 --> 00:33:56,773
but you're not gonna get
very far in life by lying.

652
00:33:57,567 --> 00:34:00,181
That is not who we are.

653
00:34:02,278 --> 00:34:04,213
Showtime.

654
00:34:07,987 --> 00:34:10,882
Stay here and don't move.

655
00:34:14,737 --> 00:34:19,173
Shall I ask questions, or do you
want to just tell me what you know?

656
00:34:19,187 --> 00:34:22,701
Well, we were all at the
Rack on tuesday night,

657
00:34:22,715 --> 00:34:27,441
and we just realized that
we all saw the same thing--

658
00:34:27,457 --> 00:34:30,431
someone talking to Carlo
Medina from "Isabella."

659
00:34:30,446 --> 00:34:34,402
Now as much as it hurts
us to rat out a friend,

660
00:34:34,415 --> 00:34:36,241
we have to tell you.

661
00:34:36,278 --> 00:34:38,242
It was Fat Carol.

662
00:34:38,257 --> 00:34:39,750
I saw her, too.

663
00:34:39,768 --> 00:34:42,763
Fat Carol leaked the spread.

664
00:34:44,275 --> 00:34:46,112
Betty?

665
00:34:46,677 --> 00:34:49,330
Is that what you saw?

666
00:34:56,238 --> 00:34:57,862
No.

667
00:34:58,628 --> 00:35:00,451
It was me.

668
00:35:04,255 --> 00:35:06,831
I told Carlo everything.

669
00:35:18,835 --> 00:35:20,550
You can go.

670
00:35:21,446 --> 00:35:23,041
What?!

671
00:35:23,188 --> 00:35:25,130
Aren't you gonna fire her?

672
00:35:25,145 --> 00:35:28,401
If I fire her, Amanda,
I'd have to fire all of you.

673
00:35:28,417 --> 00:35:30,861
You're not the only
one with informants.

674
00:35:30,878 --> 00:35:33,032
I know exactly what happened.

675
00:35:33,045 --> 00:35:35,893
The three of you might have
leaked a portion of the spread,

676
00:35:35,907 --> 00:35:39,111
but that disgusting Fat Carol

677
00:35:39,127 --> 00:35:40,740
slept with Carlo

678
00:35:40,757 --> 00:35:42,900
and spilled everything.

679
00:35:42,918 --> 00:35:45,632
- He slept with Fat Carol?!
- He slept with Fat Carol?!

680
00:35:45,647 --> 00:35:48,470
He did what he had to
do for his magazine.

681
00:35:48,485 --> 00:35:50,893
So what happens now?

682
00:35:50,908 --> 00:35:54,802
Well, I'll consider
the last day and a half your punishment.

683
00:35:54,948 --> 00:35:59,743
You were drunk, you were horny
and you were... naive.

684
00:36:01,007 --> 00:36:03,620
Fat Carol on the other hand,

685
00:36:03,637 --> 00:36:05,801
gave it up intentionally.

686
00:36:05,815 --> 00:36:08,373
She gets the axe.

687
00:36:09,467 --> 00:36:12,002
Now go before I change my mind.

688
00:36:12,016 --> 00:36:13,740
Go!

689
00:36:24,285 --> 00:36:27,163
It's Christmas in october.

690
00:36:28,677 --> 00:36:30,372
Oh, my god!

691
00:36:30,385 --> 00:36:33,591
It's just like "Top Model,"
except no one's crying.

692
00:36:34,255 --> 00:36:36,531
Justin, go sit in that chair
and don't talk to anybody

693
00:36:36,546 --> 00:36:38,620
unless they talk to you first.

694
00:36:38,638 --> 00:36:40,623
So Wilhelmina told
me what happened.

695
00:36:40,637 --> 00:36:43,703
Daniel, I'm sorry...
for everything.

696
00:36:43,718 --> 00:36:46,502
You know,
it's okay to hide things sometimes,

697
00:36:46,516 --> 00:36:49,753
especially if not hiding
them means I might lose you.

698
00:36:51,295 --> 00:36:53,193
Here.

699
00:36:53,587 --> 00:36:55,023
Shoo.

700
00:36:58,596 --> 00:37:01,031
- Nice vest.
- Ralph Lauren.

701
00:37:01,046 --> 00:37:03,170
We got it half-price because
there's a small hole,

702
00:37:03,188 --> 00:37:04,410
but you can't even see it.

703
00:37:04,428 --> 00:37:07,142
So... kids at school--

704
00:37:07,156 --> 00:37:08,282
they like it?

705
00:37:08,295 --> 00:37:11,250
No. They don't really get me.

706
00:37:12,305 --> 00:37:14,100
Word of advice--

707
00:37:14,178 --> 00:37:17,473
be who you are,
wear what you want,

708
00:37:17,485 --> 00:37:20,303
just learn how to
run real fast.

709
00:37:20,735 --> 00:37:23,550
All right, everyone.
Let's go, Marc!

710
00:37:25,398 --> 00:37:28,612
We need to shoot in five.
Step it up, people.

711
00:37:28,628 --> 00:37:30,382
Hold it.

712
00:37:30,396 --> 00:37:33,092
This isn't the
concept I approved.

713
00:37:33,105 --> 00:37:38,423
I've had final say on every holiday
spread for the last 20 years.

714
00:37:38,438 --> 00:37:41,442
Some things came up last minute
that couldn't be avoided.

715
00:37:41,455 --> 00:37:43,550
Our job is to fix the
problem, Bradford,

716
00:37:43,567 --> 00:37:45,611
not to burden you with it.

717
00:37:45,627 --> 00:37:48,640
You two are so full of crap.

718
00:37:50,226 --> 00:37:52,511
Lucky for you,
it looks quite good--

719
00:37:52,525 --> 00:37:55,202
maybe even better than Fey's.

720
00:37:55,215 --> 00:37:58,173
- Okay, uh, let's--
- Hold on.

721
00:37:58,525 --> 00:38:01,453
You know,
there's one thing missing.

722
00:38:14,765 --> 00:38:16,893
Where did you find that?

723
00:38:17,206 --> 00:38:19,100
The attic.

724
00:38:19,116 --> 00:38:21,372
I remembered mom had it.

725
00:38:22,528 --> 00:38:25,903
Looks just like the one Fey had,
don't you think?

726
00:38:28,966 --> 00:38:32,563
Yes. Almost identical.

727
00:38:33,125 --> 00:38:35,240
Good job, son.

728
00:38:35,257 --> 00:38:38,961
Okay. Can we get
this thing going?

729
00:38:38,975 --> 00:38:43,681
My hair is gray, and I'm driving to the
early bird special with my blinkers on.

730
00:38:43,697 --> 00:38:45,952
What about the sand?
Isn't that from the old shoot?

731
00:38:45,965 --> 00:38:47,923
Justin.

732
00:38:48,226 --> 00:38:50,450
Say "snow."

733
00:38:52,407 --> 00:38:54,551
Snow.

734
00:39:00,526 --> 00:39:03,653
Snow is a magical blanket.

735
00:39:04,258 --> 00:39:08,673
It hides what's ugly and
makes everything beautiful.

736
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:25,222
I'm sorry,
but your father's not who he says he is.

737
00:39:25,237 --> 00:39:27,011
I don't know what
you're talking about.

738
00:39:27,026 --> 00:39:28,772
According to our records,

739
00:39:28,786 --> 00:39:32,803
Ignacio Suarez is
117 years old...

740
00:39:32,815 --> 00:39:34,001
and dead.

741
00:39:34,018 --> 00:39:36,313
Well, obviously
that's a mistake.

742
00:39:36,328 --> 00:39:37,752
Not on our end.

743
00:39:37,768 --> 00:39:40,661
The social security number
your father's been using

744
00:39:40,678 --> 00:39:43,713
belongs to somebody else.

745
00:39:47,006 --> 00:39:49,472
Suspicions have been raised.

746
00:39:49,487 --> 00:39:53,443
father and son are being
driven further apart.

747
00:39:53,458 --> 00:39:55,813
We couldn't have
planned it any better.

748
00:40:00,565 --> 00:40:02,583
Wilhelmina Slater.

749
00:40:02,938 --> 00:40:04,800
Carlo Medina.

750
00:40:04,815 --> 00:40:07,900
It is an honor to finally
meet the legend in person.

751
00:40:08,115 --> 00:40:11,380
I see I should add shameless
suck-up to the list.

752
00:40:11,398 --> 00:40:12,583
What list is that?

753
00:40:12,595 --> 00:40:17,021
I asked you here to tell you
you are an underhanded bastard,

754
00:40:17,035 --> 00:40:19,702
a despicable, slimy weasel.

755
00:40:19,718 --> 00:40:21,623
You have no moral compass,

756
00:40:21,637 --> 00:40:25,171
are utterly without scruples
and will use anyone in your path

757
00:40:25,185 --> 00:40:27,100
to get what you want.

758
00:40:27,867 --> 00:40:30,791
How can I entice you
to work at "Mode"?

759
00:40:30,807 --> 00:40:34,253
Or rather spy for "Mode"?

760
00:40:35,646 --> 00:40:39,163
And I want you home
